<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-7261] Disable IPV6 for junit tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7261</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;IPV6 addresses not handles currently in the common library methods. IPV6 can return address as &quot;0:0:0:0:0:0:port&quot;. Some utility methods such as NetUtils#createSocketAddress(), NetUtils#normalizeHostName(), NetUtils#getHostNameOfIp() to name a few, do not handle IPV6 address and expect address to be of format host:port.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Until IPV6 is formally supported, I propose disabling IPV6 for junit tests to avoid problems seen in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HDFS-1891&quot; title=&quot;TestBackupNode fails intermittently&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HDFS-1891&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HDFS-1891&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12506342">HADOOP-7261</key>
